Hi Everyone! My name is May Ward. I’m a one-person marketing team for a financial advising firm currently and I am so excited to be here connecting with you all!:wave::skin-tone-5:

I gained my love for content, data, and strategy while working at a top Technical SEO and content marketing agency in my area before moving in-house. I’m always looking to grow my skills, so if you have any insights or tips for a young professional in this space let me know!

*Random/fun fact* :nerd_face: I’m originally from Ethiopia and was adopted when I was 9, so during the pandemic I’ve been working on reconnecting with my heritage, and learning/remembering Amharic again! 

If you have any questions or want to connect on LinkedIn, reach out!

text:
Hello hello! I am Maylee, from Winnipeg, Manitoba (Canada). I'm the Director of Marketing for a company called Scootaround, focused on building their B2C brand in rentals and sales of mobility equipment. I learned about Superpath from a connection I made in another group and am excited to be a part of this community!

I'm one of those constant learners - if I don't know how to do something, I will look it up and figure it out. I'm very data-focused, I enjoy building well-rounded (data-centric/measurable) marketing strategies for brands and most importantly the leadership side of my job. I am still fairly new to ecom., coming from six years in CPG, and love this opportunity to share ideas, insights and best practices with others in the field.

Outside of work, I'm an avid baker, an aspiring DIY-er and gardener. Also a hardcore dog mom :wink:

Looking forward to making some connections!

text:
Hi! I'm Sam from St. Pete, Florida. I'm finishing up a 4-year stint as content marketing manager at Fulcrum, a B2B SaaS company, and soon to start my new gig at Animalz, where I learned about Superpath!

I spent the first half of my career in journalism (Tampa Bay Times) -- you can guess how that played out. I've been in content marketing for the last 7 years, and I'm here to learn (and to make friends, always). Which is to say: I'm a writer with a lot to learn about strategy, and I'm eager to do so!

Happy to be here! Send me alllllllll your dog pics.
